Package entities

Class HorseJockey

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • entities.HorseJockey

  • public class HorseJockey
extends java.lang.Thread
    Implementation of a pair Horse/Jockey, the main horse race character. This entity, belonging to the entities package, represents one of N pairs in a competition, being the bets target (by the Spectator) and having its conduct coordinated by the Broker.
    Since:
    0.1
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Hugo Fragata, Rui Lopes
    See Also:
    Broker, Spectator

    • Constructor Detail

      • HorseJockey

        public HorseJockey​(int identification,
                   int ability,
                   BettingCentre bettingCentre,
                   ControlCentre controlCentre,
                   Paddock paddock,
                   RacingTrack racingTrack,
                   Stable stable,
                   GeneralInformationRepository repository)
        Creates a pair Horse/Jockey.
        This constructor creates a pair Horse/Jockey giving the reference of the BettingCentre, ControlCentre, RacingTrack, the Paddock and Stable where is about to work on. More, the pair Horse/Jockey is also created having in mind a General Repository of Information (GeneralInformationRepository) - where all the actions must be reported and logged - and a given maximum ability ability and identification identification.
        Parameters:
        identification - number which identifies this pair Horse/Jockey.
        ability - number with characterizes the Horse maximum ability to run.
        bettingCentre - An instance of a BettingCentre where this pair Horse/Jockey will work on.
        controlCentre - An instance of a ControlCentre where this pair Horse/Jockey will work on.
        paddock - An instance of a Paddock where this pair Horse/Jockey will work on.
        racingTrack - An instance of a RacingTrack where this pair Horse/Jockey will work on.
        stable - An instance of a Stable where this Broker pair Horse/Jockey work on.
        repository - An instance of a GeneralInformationRepository in order to report all the actions and log each and every moment.

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run​()
        Definition of the HorseJockey's lifecycle. In a technical perspective this is reasoned by a thread definition function which resumes all the specifications of a HorseJockey pair, since its displacement from the Paddock, to the Stable, passing by the RacingTrack and the ControlCentre.
        Overrides:
        run in class java.lang.Thread

      • setHorseJockeyState

        public void setHorseJockeyState​(HorseJockeyState state)
        Sets the HorseJockey's state, from the possible available HorseJockeyState enumeration. Here all the actions are reported to the General Repository of Information and a new snapshot is created.
        Parameters:
        state - Enumeration value represented by HorseJockeyState
